== CONTEXT DUMP: 20-cli-foundation ==
== Task: CLI Foundation & Config ==
== Date: 2026-03-22 ==

=== TASK DESCRIPTION ===
Build the CLI binary with clap command structure, configuration loading, and API client.
The CLI shares types with the server via the api-types crate.

=== WHAT WAS BUILT ===

1. Configuration system (crates/cli/src/config.rs)
   - CliConfig struct with control_plane_url, api_key, wake_url, wake_script
   - ConfigFile struct for YAML deserialization
   - Precedence: CLI flags > env vars > config file (~/.config/remote-harness/config.yaml)
   - Env vars: REMOTE_HARNESS_URL, CONTROL_PLANE_URL, REMOTE_HARNESS_API_KEY, API_KEY, WAKE_URL, WAKE_SCRIPT
   - require_url() and require_api_key() methods for validation
   - display() method for `config show` output with masked API key

2. API Client (crates/cli/src/api_client.rs)
   - Generic HTTP methods: get, post, patch, delete with auth header
   - Connection error handling with wake URL/script suggestion
   - Error response parsing (ApiError JSON -> human-readable stderr)
   - Endpoint methods for: sessions, logs, workers, credentials, API keys, inbox, wake, health

3. Full clap command structure (crates/cli/src/main.rs)
   - Global --url and --api-key flags
   - Commands: config show, session (start/list/show/delete), attach, logs (tail/delete),
     workers (list/clear), credentials (show/set), api-key (create/list/revoke),
     inbox (send/list), wake
   - All errors go to stderr with exit code 1
   - Workflow type parsing (chat, loop_n, loop_until_sentinel, inbox)

4. Updated Cargo.toml with new dependencies: serde_yaml, dirs, anyhow, tempfile (dev)

